  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\n\nIf paste to the input field a message with a length of 4096 chars, it will be impossible to continue typing. But if delete one char, type `@`, and select any mention from the suggestions list, it will be inserted into the message, although its length will be >4096 chars.\n\nAlso, if send a message containing >30 mentions it will be sent, but **will never be received by the recipient**, as well as the '4096 chars+mention' message.\n\n<img width=\"236\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-02-03 at 16 39 03\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/106770505-59786500-663e-11eb-8744-def1d70683a8.png\">\n\n#### Expected behavior\n\n- Cannot send any message longer than 4096 chars\n- Messages with a lot of mentions are shortened, as well as plain-text ones\n\n#### Actual behavior\n\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/106770935-bf64ec80-663e-11eb-95a7-38a3f446a8a2.mp4\n\n### Reproduction\n\nCase 1:\n- Open chat\n- Paste message 4096 chars long\n- Delete last char\n- Type `@`\n- Select any mention from the list\n- Send the message and check it on another device\n\nCase 2:\n- Enter more than 30 mentions to the input field\n- Send the message\n- Check the recipient's device\n\n### Additional Information\n\n- Status version: Nightly 03/02\n- Operating System: Android, iOS",
